The paper discusses bibliometrics and citation rates, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. However, the focus on Web of Science and linked database records suggests a stronger connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The analysis of references and citation rates also relates to computational linguistics (cs.CL) and social media (cs.SI), as well as cybersecurity (cs.CY) which may involve analyzing citation patterns in academic literature.
